{'function': {'name': 'GITHUB_ADD_OR_UPDATE_TEAM_PROJECT_PERMISSIONS', 'description': "Adds a classic project to a team or updates the team's permission on it. This endpoint grants or updates permissions for a team on a specific classic project (not Projects V2). The authenticated user must have admin permissions for the project. Both the team and project must belong to the same organization. Requirements: - The project must be a classic project (not GitHub Projects V2) - The authenticated user must have admin permissions on the project - The team and project must be in the same organization - Requires 'admin:org' scope for the authentication token Returns HTTP 204 No Content on success, 403 if project is not an org project, or 404 if the organization, team, or project is not found.", 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'AddOrUpdateTeamProjectPermissionsRequest', 'required': ['org', 'team_slug', 'project_id'], 'properties': {'org': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Org', 'examples': ['octo-org', 'my-company'], 'description': 'The organization name (login) that owns both the team and the classic project. Case-insensitive. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Organization', 'human_parameter_description': "The GitHub organization that contains both the team and the classic project you want to manage. Enter the org handle (e.g., 'octo-org')."}, 'team_slug': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Team Slug', 'examples': ['justice-league', 'engineering', 'frontend-team'], 'description': "The team's URL-friendly slug identifier within the organization. Found in the team's URL path. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Team Slug', 'human_parameter_description': "The team's slug (URL-friendly name) within the organization. You can find this in the team's URL (e.g., for github.com/orgs/my-org/teams/my-team, the slug is 'my-team')."}, 'permission': {'enum': ['read', 'write', 'admin'], 'type': 'string', 'title': 'PermissionEnm', 'examples': ['read', 'write', 'admin'], 'description': "Permission level to grant the team: 'read' (view only), 'write' (view and edit), or 'admin' (full control including settings). If omitted, uses the team's default permission. Please provide a value of type string.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Permission Level', 'human_parameter_description': "Choose the access level for the team: 'read' (view only), 'write' (can edit), or 'admin' (full control). Leave blank to use the team's default permission."}, 'project_id': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'Project Id', 'examples': [1002604, 12345678], 'description': 'The unique numeric ID of the classic project. This is NOT the project number displayed in the UI. Please provide a value of type integer. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Project ID', 'human_parameter_description': "The numeric ID of the classic project (not Projects V2). You can get this from the 'List organization projects' or 'List team projects' actions. Note: This is the internal ID, not the project number shown in the GitHub UI."}}, 'description': "Grants or updates a team's permissions for a specific classic project (not Projects V2).\n\nNote: This endpoint works with GitHub's classic Projects feature. The project\nmust be a classic project (not Projects V2), and both the team and project must\nbelong to the same organization. The authenticated user needs admin permissions\non the project."}, 'strict': None}, 'type': 'function'}
