ue of type string.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Range Segment ID', 'human_parameter_description': "If needed, provide the ID of a specific segment like a header, footer, or footnote. If you're working with the main body of the document, you can leave this blank."}, 'rangeStartIndex': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'Range Start Index', 'minimum': 0, 'examples': [100], 'description': 'The zero-based start index of the range. Please provide a value of type integer. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Range Start Index', 'human_parameter_description': 'Specify the starting point of the range in the document. This index tells the system where to begin including content in the named range.'}}}, 'strict': None}, 'type': 'function'}
{'function': {'name': 'GOOGLEDOCS_CREATE_PARAGRAPH_BULLETS', 'description': 'Tool to add bullets to paragraphs within a specified range in a Google Document. Use when you need to format a list or a set of paragraphs as bullet points.', 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'CreateParagraphBulletsRequestModel', 'required': ['document_id', 'createParagraphBullets'], 'properties': {'document_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Document Id', 'examples': ['12345abcdef'], 'description': 'The ID of the document to update. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Document Id', 'human_parameter_description': 'Please provide the document ID where you want to add bullet points.'}, 'createParagraphBullets': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'Create Paragraph Bullets', 'required': ['range', 'bulletPreset'], 'properties': {'range': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'Range', 'required': ['startIndex', 'endIndex'], 'properties': {'endIndex': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'End Index', 'examples': [200], 'description': 'The zero-based end index of the range, exclusive.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Endindex', 'human_parameter_description': 'Specify the endpoint of the range in the document, where the bullet formatting will stop.'}, 'segmentId': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Segment Id', 'examples': ['header_id'], 'description': "The ID of the header, footer, or footnote that this range is contained in. An empty segment ID signifies the document's body.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Segmentid', 'human_parameter_description': 'If applicable, provide the ID of a specific section, like a header or footer, where the bullets should be applied.'}, 'startIndex': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'Start Index', 'examples': [100], 'description': 'The zero-based start index of the range, inclusive.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Startindex', 'human_parameter_description': 'Provide the starting point of the range in the document where you want to apply the bullet formatting.'}}, 'description': 'The range to apply the bullet preset to.', 'additionalProperties': False, 'human_parameter_name': 'Range', 'human_parameter_description': 'The range to apply the bullet preset to.'}, 'bulletPreset': {'enum': ['BULLET_GLYPH_PRESET_UNSPECIFIED', 'BULLET_DISC_CIRCLE_SQUARE', 'BULLET_DIAMONDX_ARROW3D_SQUARE', 'BULLET_CHECKBOX', 'BULLET_ARROW_DIAMOND_DISC', 'BULLET_STAR_CIRCLE_SQUARE', 'BULLET_ARROW3D_CIRCLE_SQUARE', 'BULLET_LEFTTRIANGLE_DIAMOND_DISC', 'BULLET_DIAMONDX_HOLLOWDIAMOND_SQUARE', 'BULLET_DIAMOND_CIRCLE_SQUARE', 'NUMBERED_DECIMAL_ALPHA_ROMAN', 'NUMBERED_DECIMAL_ALPHA_ROMAN_PARENS', 'NUMBERED_DECIMAL_NESTED', 'NUMBERED_UPPERALPHA_ALPHA_ROMAN', 'NUMBERED_UPPERROMAN_UPPERALPHA_DECIMAL', 'NUMBERED_ZERODECIMAL_ALPHA_ROMAN'], 'type': 'string', 'title': 'Bullet Preset', 'examples': ['BULLET_DISC_CIRCLE_SQUARE'], 'description': 'The kinds of bullet glyphs to be used.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Bulletpreset', 'human_parameter_description': 'Choose the style of bullet points you want to use for the paragraphs.'}}, 'additionalProperties': False, 'human_parameter_name': 'Create Paragraph Bullets', 'human_parameter_description': 'The create paragraph bullets value.', 'description': 'This parameter is required.'}}}, 'strict': None}, 'type': 'function'}
{'function': {'name': 'GOOGLEDOCS_DELETE_CONTENT_RANGE', 'description': 'Tool to delete a range of content from a Google Document. Use when you need to remove a specific portion of text or other structural elements within a document. Note: Every segment (body, header, footer, footnote) in Google Docs ends with a final newline character that cannot be deleted. Ensure the endIndex does not include this trailing newline.', 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'DeleteContentRangeRequestModel', 'required': ['document_id', 'range'], 'properties': {'range': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'Range', 'properties': {'tabId': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Tab Id', 'examples': ['t.abcdef123456'], 'description': "The ID of the tab the range is in. When omitted, the request is applied to the first tab. In a document with a single tab, if provided, it must match the singular tab's ID; if omitted, it applies to the singular tab. In a multi-tab document, if provided, it applies to the specified tab; if omitted, it applies to the first tab.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Tab Id', 'human_parameter_description': 'The ID of the tab the range is in. When omitted, the request is applied to the first tab.'}, 'endIndex': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'End Index', 'examples': [200], 'description': "The zero-based end index of the range, in UTF-16 code units, relative to the beginning of the segment. IMPORTANT: Every segment in Google Docs (body, header, footer, footnote) ends with a newline character ('\\n') that cannot be deleted. The endIndex must not include this final newline. For example, if the segment's last index is 368, set endIndex to 367 to avoid including the trailing newline.", 'human_parameter_name': 'End Index', 'human_parameter_description': 'The zero-based end index of the range, in UTF-16 code units, relative to the beginning of the segment. The endIndex must not include the final newline at the end of the segment.'}, 'segmentId': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Segment Id', 'examples': ['h.1a2b3c4d5e6f', ''], 'description': "The ID of the header, footer, or footnote the range is in. An empty segment ID or omitting this field signifies the document's body.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Segment Id', 'human_parameter_description': "The ID of the header, footer, or footnote the range is in. An empty segment ID signifies the document's body."}, 'startIndex': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'Start Index', 'examples': [100], 'description': 'The zero-based start index of the range, in UTF-16 code units, relative to the beginning of the segment.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Start Index', 'human_parameter_description': 'The zero-based start index of the range, in UTF-16 code units, relative to the beginning of the segment.'}}, 'description': 'The range of content to delete. Deleting text across paragraph boundaries may merge paragraphs and affect styles. Certain deletions can invalidate document structure (e.g., part of a surrogate pair, last newline of critical elements, incomplete deletion of tables/equations). IMPORTANT: The endIndex must not include the final newline character at the end of a segment (body, header, footer, footnote), as this newline cannot be deleted. This parameter is required.', 'additionalProperties': False, 'human_parameter_name': 'Content Range', 'human_parameter_description': 'Define the start and end positions of the content to be deleted from the document. The endIndex must not include the final newline at the end of the segment.'}, 'document_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Document Id', 'examples': ['1aBcDeFgHiJkLmNoPqRsTuVwXyZ0123456789'], 'description': 'The ID of the document from which to delete content. This ID can be found in the URL of the Google Doc. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Document ID', 'human_parameter_description': 'The unique identifier of the Google Document from which content will be deleted.'}}}, 'strict': None}, 'type': 'function'}
{'function': {'name': 'GOOGLEDOCS_DELETE_FOOTER', 'description': 'Tool to delete a footer from a Google Document. Use when you need to remove a footer from a specific section or the default footer.', 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'DeleteFooterRequestModel', 'required': ['document_id', 'footer_id'], 'properties': {'tab_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Tab Id', 'examples': ['tab_abc'], 'description': 'The tab that contains the footer to delete. When omitted, the request is applied to the first tab. Please provide a value of type string.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Tab ID', 'human_parameter_description': 'The identifier for the tab that includes the footer you want to remove. If you don’t specify a tab, the first tab will be used.'}, 'footer_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Footer Id', 'description': 'The ID of the footer to delete. Footer IDs are system-generated strings created by Google Docs. Obtain a valid footer ID from: (1) GOOGLEDOCS_CREATE_FOOTER response (footer_id field), or (2) GOOGLEDOCS_GET_DOCUMENT_BY_ID (footers dictionary keys). Do not use made-up or placeholder values. If this footer is defined on DocumentStyle, the reference to this footer is removed, resulting in no footer of that type for the first section of the document. If this footer is defined on a SectionStyle, the reference to this footer is removed and the footer of that type is now continued from the previous section. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Footer ID', 'human_parameter_description': 'The unique identifier of the footer you wish to delete. Footer IDs are system-generated strings. Obtain them from GOOGLEDOCS_CREATE_FOOTER response (footer_id field) or from GOOGLEDOCS_GET_DOCUMENT_BY_ID (footers dictionary keys).'}, 'document_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Document Id', 'examples': ['12345abcdef'], 'description': 'The ID of the document to delete the footer from. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Document ID', 'human_parameter_description': 'The unique identifier of the document from which you want to remove the footer.'}}}, 'strict': None}, 'type': 'function'}
{'function': {'name': 'GOOGLEDOCS_DELETE_HEADER', 'description': 'Deletes the header from the specified section or the default header if no section is specified. Use this tool to remove a header from a Google Document.', 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'DeleteHeaderRequest', 'required': ['document_id', 'header_id'], 'properties': {'tab_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Tab Id', 'examples': ['tab_abc'], 'description': 'The tab containing the header to delete. When omitted, the request is applied to the first tab. Please provide a value of type string.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Tab ID', 'human_parameter_description': "Specify the tab where the header is located if it's not in the first tab. This ensures that you delete the header from the right place."}, 'header_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Header Id', 'examples': ['header_123'], 'description': 'The ID of the header to delete. If this header is defined on `DocumentStyle`, the reference to this header is removed, resulting in no header of that type for the first section of the document. If this header is defined on a `SectionStyle`, the reference to this header is removed and the header of that type is now continued from the previous section. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Header ID', 'human_parameter_description': 'Enter the ID of the specific header you wish to delete. This helps to accurately target the header for removal.'}, 'document_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Document Id', 'examples': ['12345abcdef'], 'description': 'The ID of the document from which to delete the header. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Document ID', 'human_parameter_description': 'Provide the ID of the document where you want to remove the header. This is essential to identify the correct document.'}}}, 'strict': None}, 'type': 'function'}
