{'function': {'name': 'GOOGLESHEETS_CLEAR_VALUES', 'description': 'Clears cell content (preserving formatting and notes) from a specified A1 notation range in a Google Spreadsheet; the range must correspond to an existing sheet and cells.', 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'ClearValuesRequest', 'required': ['spreadsheet_id', 'range'], 'properties': {'range': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Range', 'examples': ['Sheet1!A1:B10', 'Sheet2!C:D', 'A1:Z100', 'My Custom Sheet!B3:F10'], 'description': "The A1 notation of the range to clear values from (e.g., 'Sheet1!A1:B2', 'MySheet!C:C', or 'A1:D5'). If the sheet name is omitted (e.g., 'A1:B2'), the operation applies to the first visible sheet. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Range', 'human_parameter_description': 'Specify the range of cells you want to clear using A1 notation. This helps define exactly which cells will be affected in the spreadsheet.'}, 'spreadsheet_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Spreadsheet Id', 'examples': ['1qZ_g6N0g3Z0s5hJ2xQ8vP9r7T_u6X3iY2o0kE_l5N7M', 'spreαdsheetId_from_url'], 'description': 'The unique identifier of the Google Spreadsheet from which to clear values. This ID can be found in the URL of the spreadsheet. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Spreadsheet ID', 'human_parameter_description': "Provide the unique ID of the Google Spreadsheet where you want to clear data. You can find this ID in the spreadsheet's URL."}}}, 'strict': None}, 'type': 'function'}
{'function': {'name': 'GOOGLESHEETS_CREATE_CHART', 'description': 'Create a chart in a Google Sheets spreadsheet using the specified data range and chart type. Conditional requirements: - Provide either a simple chart via chart_type + data_range (basicChart), OR supply a full chart_spec supporting all chart types. Exactly one approach should be used. - When using chart_spec, set exactly one of the union fields (basicChart | pieChart | bubbleChart | candlestickChart | histogramChart | waterfallChart | treemapChart | orgChart | scorecardChart).', 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'CreateChartRequest', 'required': ['spreadsheet_id', 'sheet_id', 'chart_type', 'data_range'], 'properties': {'title': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Title', 'examples': ['Sales Data', 'Monthly Revenue'], 'description': 'Optional title for the chart. Please provide a value of type string.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Chart Title', 'human_parameter_description': 'Provide a title for the chart to give context to viewers.'}, 'sheet_id': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'Sheet Id', 'examples': [0, 123456789], 'description': "The numeric sheetId (not the sheet name/title) of the worksheet where the chart will be created. This is a unique integer identifier for the sheet within the spreadsheet. The first/default sheet typically has sheetId=0. IMPORTANT: Use 'Get Spreadsheet Info' action to retrieve valid sheetIds - look for sheets[].properties.sheetId in the response. The sheetId must exist in the target spreadsheet; using an ID from a different spreadsheet will fail. Please provide a value of type integer. This parameter is required.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Sheet ID', 'human_parameter_description': 'Enter the numeric ID of the worksheet within the spreadsheet where the chart is to be placed. Use Get Spreadsheet Info to find valid sheet IDs.'}, 'subtitle': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Subtitle', 'examples': ['Q1 2024', 'Year over Year'], 'description': 'Optional subtitle for the chart. Please provide a value of type string.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Chart Subtitle', 'human_parameter_description': 'Add a subtitle to provide additional context for the chart.'}, 'chart_spec': {'type': 'object', 'title': 'Chart Spec', 'examples': [{'pieChart': {'domain': {'sourceRange': {'sources': [{'sheetId': 0, 'endRowIndex': 5, 'startRowIndex': 0, 'endColumnIndex': 1, 'startColumnIndex': 0}]}}, 'series': {'sourceRange': {'sources': [{'sheetId': 0, 'endRowIndex': 5, 'startRowIndex': 0, 'endColumnIndex': 2, 'startColumnIndex': 1}]}}, 'legendPosition': 'RIGHT_LEGEND'}}], 'description': 'Optional full ChartSpec object to send to the Google Sheets API. Use this to support ALL chart types and advanced options. Must set exactly one of: basicChart, pieChart, bubbleChart, candlestickChart, histogramChart, treemapChart, waterfallChart, orgChart, scorecardChart. See https://developers.google.com/workspace/sheets/api/reference/rest/v4/spreadsheets/charts#ChartSpec.', 'additionalProperties': True, 'human_parameter_name': 'Chart Spec', 'human_parameter_description': 'Optionally, provide a detailed chart specification for more advanced charting options.'}, 'chart_type': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Chart Type', 'examples': ['COLUMN', 'LINE', 'BAR', 'AREA', 'PIE', 'SCATTER', 'COMBO'], 'description': 'The type of chart to create. Case-insensitive. Supported types: BAR, LINE, AREA, COLUMN, SCATTER, COMBO, STEPPED_AREA (basic charts with axes), PIE (pie/donut charts), HISTOGRAM, BUBBLE, CANDLESTICK (requires 4+ data columns for low/open/close/high), TREEMAP, WATERFALL, ORG (organizational charts), SCORECARD. Each chart type uses its appropriate Google Sheets API spec structure. For advanced customization, provide chart_spec instead. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Chart Type', 'human_parameter_description': 'Specify the type of chart you want to create from the available options.'}, 'data_range': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Data Range', 'examples': ['A1:C10', 'Sheet1!B2:D20', 'Data!A1:E50'], 'description': "A single contiguous range of data for the chart in A1 notation (e.g., 'A1:C10' or 'Sheet1!B2:D20'). Must be a single continuous range - comma-separated multi-ranges (e.g., 'A1:A10,C1:C10') are not supported. When chart_spec is not provided, the first column is used as the domain/labels and the remaining columns as series. IMPORTANT: PIE charts require at least 2 columns - the first column for category labels (domain) and the second column for numeric values (series). Single-column ranges are not supported for PIE charts. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Data Range', 'human_parameter_description': 'Provide the range of data you want to include in the chart using A1 notation.'}, 'x_axis_title': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'X Axis Title', 'examples': ['Time Period', 'Categories'], 'description': 'Optional title for the X-axis. Please provide a value of type string.', 'human_parameter_name': 'X-axis Title', 'human_parameter_description': 'Provide a title for the X-axis to clarify what the data represents.'}, 'y_axis_title': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Y Axis Title', 'examples': ['Revenue ($)', 'Count'], 'description': 'Optional title for the Y-axis. Please provide a value of type string.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Y-axis Title', 'human_parameter_description': 'Provide a title for the Y-axis to define the values shown on that axis.'}, 'background_red': {'type': 'number', 'title': 'Background Red', 'examples': [0, 0.5, 1], 'description': 'Red component of chart background color (0.0-1.0). If not specified, uses default. Please provide a value of type number.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Background Red', 'human_parameter_description': "Set the red color value for the chart's background (0.0 being none and 1.0 being fully red)."}, 'spreadsheet_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Spreadsheet Id', 'examples': ['1BxiMVs0XRA5nFMdKvBdBZjgmUUqptlbs74OgvE2upms'], 'description': "The unique identifier of the Google Sheets spreadsheet where the chart will be created. Must be the actual spreadsheet ID from the URL (e.g., '1BxiMVs0XRA5nFMdKvBdBZjgmUUqptlbs74OgvE2upms'), NOT the spreadsheet name or title. Find it in the URL: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/SPREADSHEET_ID/edit. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Spreadsheet ID', 'human_parameter_description': 'Provide the unique ID of the Google Sheets spreadsheet where you want to create your chart. Use the ID from the URL, not the spreadsheet name.'}, 'background_blue': {'type': 'number', 'title': 'Background Blue', 'examples': [0, 0.5, 1], 'description': 'Blue component of chart background color (0.0-1.0). If not specified, uses default. Please provide a value of type number.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Background Blue', 'human_parameter_description': "Set the blue color value for the chart's background (0.0 being none and 1.0 being fully blue)."}, 'legend_position': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Legend Position', 'default': 'BOTTOM_LEGEND', 'examples': ['BOTTOM_LEGEND', 'RIGHT_LEGEND', 'NO_LEGEND'], 'description': 'Position of the chart legend. Options: BOTTOM_LEGEND, TOP_LEGEND, LEFT_LEGEND, RIGHT_LEGEND, NO_LEGEND. Please provide a value of type string.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Legend Position', 'human_parameter_description': 'Choose where you want the legend to appear in relation to the chart.'}, 'background_green': {'type': 'number', 'title': 'Background Green', 'examples': [0, 0.5, 1], 'description': 'Green component of chart background color (0.0-1.0). If not specified, uses default. Please provide a value of type number.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Background Green', 'human_parameter_description': "Set the green color value for the chart's background (0.0 being none and 1.0 being fully green)."}}}, 'strict': None}, 'type': 'function'}
