ex number to insert it elsewhere.'}, 'spreadsheet_id': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Spreadsheet Id', 'examples': ['1qpyC0XzHc_-_d824s2VfopkHh7D0jW4aXCS1D_AlGA'], 'description': "The unique identifier of the Google Spreadsheet. Can be provided as the ID (e.g., '1qpyC0XzHc_-_d824s2VfopkHh7D0jW4aXCS1D_AlGA') or as a full URL (the ID will be extracted automatically). Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Spreadsheet ID', 'human_parameter_description': "Provide the ID of the Google Spreadsheet where you want to add a new row. You can find it in the spreadsheet's URL, or paste the full URL and the ID will be extracted automatically."}, 'response_ranges': {'type': 'array', 'items': {'type': 'string', 'properties': {}}, 'title': 'Response Ranges', 'examples': [['Sheet1!A1:D10'], ['Sheet1!A:A', 'Sheet2!B:B']], 'description': "Limits the ranges included in the response spreadsheet. Only meaningful when include_spreadsheet_in_response is True. Use A1 notation (e.g., ['Sheet1!A1:D10']).", 'human_parameter_name': 'Response Ranges', 'human_parameter_description': 'Optionally limit the response to specific ranges of the spreadsheet. Only applies when include_spreadsheet_in_response is True.'}, 'inherit_from_before': {'type': 'boolean', 'title': 'Inherit From Before', 'default': False, 'examples': [True, False], 'description': 'If True, the newly inserted row will inherit formatting and properties from the row immediately preceding its insertion point. If False, it will have default formatting. Please provide a value of type boolean.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Inherit formatting from previous row?', 'human_parameter_description': "Decide if the new row should take on the style of the row right before it. Choose 'Yes' to carry over formatting, or 'No' for a default look."}, 'response_include_grid_data': {'type': 'boolean', 'title': 'Response Include Grid Data', 'examples': [True, False], 'description': 'If True, grid data will 