a value of type integer.", 'human_parameter_name': 'End Row Index', 'human_parameter_description': 'The end row (0-indexed, exclusive) of the range.'}, 'rangeSheetId': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'Range Sheet Id', 'examples': [0, 123456789], 'description': "The numeric sheet ID for a GridRange-based search. Required when using the 'range' parameter with A1 notation. Can also be used alone or with row/column index parameters to define a specific range. Mutually exclusive with sheet_id and all_sheets. Please provide a value of type integer.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Range Sheet Id', 'human_parameter_description': 'The sheet ID for GridRange-based search.'}, 'searchByRegex': {'type': 'boolean', 'title': 'Search By Regex', 'default': False, 'examples': [True, False], 'description': 'Whether to treat the find text as a regular expression. Please provide a value of type boolean.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Search By Regex', 'human_parameter_description': 'Whether to treat the find text as a regular expression.'}, 'spreadsheetId': {'type': 'string', 'title': 'Spreadsheet Id', 'examples': ['1BxiMVs0XRA5nFMdKvBdBZjgmUUqptlbs74OgvE2upms'], 'description': 'The ID of the spreadsheet to update. Please provide a value of type string. This parameter is required.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Spreadsheet Id', 'human_parameter_description': 'The ID of the spreadsheet to update.'}, 'startRowIndex': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'Start Row Index', 'examples': [0, 5, 10], 'description': "The start row (0-indexed, inclusive) of the range. Only used when range_sheet_id is provided without a 'range' parameter. Please provide a value of type integer.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Start Row Index', 'human_parameter_description': 'The start row (0-indexed, inclusive) of the range.'}, 'endColumnIndex': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'End Column Index', 'examples': [3, 10, 26], 'description': "The end column (0-indexed, exclusive) of the range. Column A = 0, B = 1, etc. Only used when range_sheet_id is provided without a 'range' parameter. Please provide a value of type integer.", 'human_parameter_name': 'End Column Index', 'human_parameter_description': 'The end column (0-indexed, exclusive) of the range.'}, 'includeFormulas': {'type': 'boolean', 'title': 'Include Formulas', 'examples': [True, False], 'description': 'Whether to include cells with formulas in the search. If true, formulas are searched and can be replaced. If false, only cell values (not formulas) are searched. If not specified, the default API behavior applies (both formulas and values are searched). Please provide a value of type boolean.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Include Formulas', 'human_parameter_description': 'Whether to include cells containing formulas in the search.'}, 'matchEntireCell': {'type': 'boolean', 'title': 'Match Entire Cell', 'default': False, 'examples': [True, False], 'description': 'Whether to match only cells that contain the entire search term. Please provide a value of type boolean.', 'human_parameter_name': 'Match Entire Cell', 'human_parameter_description': 'Whether to match only cells that contain the entire search term.'}, 'startColumnIndex': {'type': 'integer', 'title': 'Start Column Index', 'examples': [0, 2, 5], 'description': "The start column (0-indexed, inclusive) of the range. Column A = 0, B = 1, etc. Only used when range_sheet_id is provided without a 'range' parameter. Please provide a value of type integer.", 'human_parameter_name': 'Start Column Index', 'human_parameter_description': 'The start column (0-indexed, inclusive) of the range.'}}}, 'strict': None}, 'type': 'function'}
